18/10/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Prior to the start of his official three-day visit to Tirana on Monday (18 October), Greek President Costis Stephanopoulos told Albanian media that he expects the visit to boost bilateral relations.
According to Stephanopoulos, bilateral ties have improved considerably in recent years because of mutual confidence, respect and understanding.
He reaffirmed Greek support for the reform process in the neighbouring country as well as for Albania's Euro-Atlantic bid.
(Kathimerini - 18/10/04;
Albanian News - 16/10/04)
